- "Low stock" refers to products with an inventory level less than or equal to the reorder level;
- "Highly rated" means the average rating is 4 or higher;
- "Customers who have spent a lot" refers to customers who have spent more than $1000.

- "Highly rated" refers to products with an average rating of 4 or higher;
- "Popular" refers to products with a total quantity sold greater than 100;
- "Most recent review" is determined by the latest `created_at` date in the `reviews` table.

- 'top 5 revenue-generating products' refers to the products with the highest total revenue;
- 'customer satisfaction scores' refers to the average ratings given by customers;
- 'shining brightest' is a metaphor for generating the most revenue.

- 'Delivered' refers to orders that have been successfully delivered to the customers;
- 'Total revenue' is calculated as the sum of the discounted price multiplied by the quantity for each product;
- 'Average rating' is based on customer reviews and is a measure of customer satisfaction.

- "Guardians of feedback" refers to the top 3 customers who have written the most reviews;
- "Gems of the product catalog" refers to the top 3 products with the highest average ratings;
- "Common ranking" means the rank of the reviewer matches the rank of the product.

- 'Shining stars' refers to products with an average rating greater than 4;
- 'Standing tall' indicates that these products are notable or prominent;
- 'Bounty of orders' refers to the total quantity of products ordered;
- The categories are ordered by the total quantity ordered, with the most ordered categories appearing first.

- "blossoming products" refers to products that have the highest profits;
- "admiration of their customers" refers to high average ratings;
- "fruitful profits" and "significant revenue" refer to the total profit and total revenue of the products.

- "Shining stars" refers to products with the highest average ratings;
- "Earned the highest praise from customers" refers to products with the highest average ratings;
- "Generated more than a thousand dollars in revenue" refers to categories with a total revenue greater than 1000.
